{"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GAsyncResult"},{"type":"text","text":" provides a base class for implementing asynchronous function results."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AsyncResultProtocol","kind":"identifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"text":"PointerWrapper","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PointerWrapperP"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Asynchronous operations are broken up into two separate operations"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"which are chained together by a "},{"code":"GAsyncReadyCallback","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". To begin"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"an asynchronous operation, provide a ","type":"text"},{"code":"GAsyncReadyCallback","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"asynchronous function. This callback will be triggered when the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"operation has completed, and must be run in a later iteration of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the thread-default main context (see","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.push_thread_default","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"]) from where the operation was","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"initiated. It will be passed a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GAsyncResult"},{"type":"text","text":" instance filled with the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"details of the operation’s success or failure, the object the asynchronous","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"function was started for and any error codes returned. The asynchronous"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"callback function is then expected to call the corresponding "},{"code":"_finish()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"function, passing the object the function was called for, the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"GAsyncResult","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance, and (optionally) an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"error"},{"text":" to grab any","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"error conditions that may have occurred."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"_finish()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function for an operation takes the generic result","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(of type ","type":"text"},{"code":"GAsyncResult","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":") and returns the specific result that the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"operation in question yields (e.g. a [class"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileEnumerator","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] for a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"“enumerate children” operation). If the result or error status of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"operation is not needed, there is no need to call the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_finish()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"function; GIO will take care of cleaning up the result and error","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"information after the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GAsyncReadyCallback"},{"type":"text","text":" returns. You can pass"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NULL"},{"type":"text","text":" for the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GAsyncReadyCallback"},{"type":"text","text":" if you don’t need to take any"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"action at all after the operation completes. Applications may also","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"take a reference to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GAsyncResult"},{"type":"text","text":" and call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_finish()"},{"type":"text","text":" later;"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"however, the "},{"code":"_finish()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function may be called at most once.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Example of a typical asynchronous operation flow:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"c","type":"codeListing","code":["void _theoretical_frobnitz_async (Theoretical         *t,","                                  GCancellable        *c,","                                  GAsyncReadyCallback  cb,","                                  gpointer             u);","","gboolean _theoretical_frobnitz_finish (Theoretical   *t,","                                       GAsyncResult  *res,","                                       GError       **e);","","static void","frobnitz_result_func (GObject      *source_object,","\t\t GAsyncResult *res,","\t\t gpointer      user_data)","{","  gboolean success = FALSE;","","  success = _theoretical_frobnitz_finish (source_object, res, NULL);","","  if (success)","    g_printf (\"Hurray!\\n\");","  else","    g_printf (\"Uh oh!\\n\");","","  ...","","}","","int main (int argc, void *argv[])","{","   ...","","   _theoretical_frobnitz_async (theoretical_data,","                                NULL,","                                frobnitz_result_func,","                                NULL);","","   ...","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The callback for an asynchronous operation is called only once, and is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"always called, even in the case of a cancelled operation. On cancellation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the result is a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_IO_ERROR_CANCELLED"},{"text":" error.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"I\/O Priority","anchor":"IO-Priority","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Many I\/O-related asynchronous operations have a priority parameter,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"which is used in certain cases to determine the order in which","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"operations are executed. They are not used to determine system-wide"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"I\/O scheduling. Priorities are integers, with lower numbers indicating","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"higher priority. It is recommended to choose priorities between","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_PRIORITY_LOW"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"G_PRIORITY_HIGH","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", with "},{"code":"G_PRIORITY_DEFAULT","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"as a default."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResultProtocol","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying "},{"code":"GAsyncResult","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResult","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Alternatively, use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResultRef"},{"type":"text","text":" as a lighweight, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO"]]},"metadata":{"symbolKind":"protocol","title":"AsyncResultProtocol","externalID":"s:3GIO19AsyncResultProtocolP","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AsyncResultProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"AsyncResultProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"roleHeading":"Protocol"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResultProtocol","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Instance-Properties","title":"Instance Properties","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResultProtocol\/async_result_ptr-3aza","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResultProtocol\/sourceObject","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResultProtocol\/userData"]},{"anchor":"Instance-Methods","generated":true,"title":"Instance Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResultProtocol\/appInfoGetDefaultForTypeFinish()","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResultProtocol\/appInfoGetDefaultForURISchemeFinish()","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResultProtocol\/appInfoLaunchDefaultForURIFinish()","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResultProtocol\/busGetFinish()","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResultProtocol\/dbusAddressGetStreamFinish(outGuid:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResultProtocol\/fileNewTmpDirFinish()","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResultProtocol\/fileNewTmpFinish(iostream:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResultProtocol\/getSourceObject()","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResultProtocol\/getUserData()","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResultProtocol\/isTagged(sourceTag:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResultProtocol